cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper presents a probabilistic modeling framework and adaptive sampling algorithm for input design, which involves mapping from input design space to a distribution over a property of interest. This problem is commonly encountered in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of stochastic oracles, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
